:figcap.Categories of Bookshelves
:efig.
:p.This is a list of categories of bookshelves. Each category contains
a list of one or more bookshelves.  The :hp2.Default Bookshelves:ehp2.
category contains a list of all available bookshelves. The other
categories are subsets of the default.
:h3.FINDing a Category
:p.You can scroll through this list. Or you can enter a
:hp2.FIND:ehp2. (:hp2.F:ehp2.) command for some character string in the
category descriptions.  The :hp2.FIND:ehp2. command operand may contain
blanks.  You can also use the :hp2.RFIND:ehp2. command (usually
:rk.F5:erk. or :rk.F17:erk.).
:h3.Selecting a Category
:p.You can select a category by placing the cursor next to it and
pressing the :rk.Enter:erk. key. You can optionally type a nonblank
character.
.cp
