:hp7.blksize:ehp7.. This list is also ordered with the best matches
first.
.cp
:h4.Pop-up Window and the Cancel Key
:p."List All Books with Matches" is another pop-up window. You have now
moved downward vertically
:rev refid=one.
:hp1.two levels:ehp2. in the panel hierarchy. If you change your mind
and press the :hp2.Cancel:ehp2. key the "Set Up Search" panel will be
displayed, and you must press :hp2.Cancel:ehp2. a second time.  Note
that there is no :hp2.Exit:ehp2. key.
:erev refid=one.
:h3.Selecting a Book
:p.You can select a book by placing the cursor on the desired book and
pressing the :rk.Enter:erk. key.
:rev refid=one.
This will move downward vertically.
:erev refid=one.
You will then see the same "List All Topics with Matches" window as when
you searched an individual book.
:rev refid=one.
:p.For example, if you select MVS/ESA V4 JCL Reference, you will see:
:fig.
:screen.
 .-----------------------------------------------------------------------------.
 |                        List All Topics with Matches                         |
 | Command ===> ____________________________________________ SCROLL ===> CSR   |
 |                                                                             |
 | Fuzzy matches for: blksize                                                  |
